One of the main examples is The Smashing Pumpkins, a popular alternative rock band from Chicago, Illinois, whose music makes it so desirable and appealing to teenagers.

They do not have the best voice. They don’t have huge concerts. The things they do have, however, are support from Billboard and MTV and authenticity. Tommy February6 has a strong online presence across certain social media platforms—the brand, much like Everything Goes Nihon, connects well with its audience through Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and Google+.

But what Usain Bolt and Jessica Ennis don’t tell the kids out there waiting is the long, hungry hours, the hours of compromise, the training, the slips, and the bruises; everything they should have faced. It only seems as if the kids are succeeding, but really, they’re just sleepwalking to a mediocre, lovelorn nocturne. They should really open their hearts, well, to funk.

WANTED: A Talented Rap Sheet Artist

¶ By Rachel Boris, Fall 2011
